```json
{
  "application": "SLURM",
  "details": {
    "resources": {
      "nodes": 2,
      "tasks_per_node": 2,
      "gpus": "a100:2",
      "memory": "32G",
      "cores": 32,
      "time": "0-02:00:00"
    },
    "modules": {
      "system": "cesga/system",
      "miniconda3": "miniconda3/22.11",
      "conda_env": "mytorchdist"
    },
    "script": "mnist.sh"
  }
}
```

This script is running within the **SLURM** workload manager. The script requests two nodes, two tasks per node, two A100 GPUs per node, 32 GB of memory per node, 32 cores per node, and a runtime of two hours. It also loads the `cesga/system` and `miniconda3/22.11` modules, activates a conda environment named `mytorchdist`, and runs a script called `mnist.sh` using the `srun` command.
